The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, June 04, 2004 				 KEC back in black
																								Mumbai, June 3 (PTI): KEC International, the RPG group company, has reported a turnaround with a consolidated net profit of Rs 24.21 crore for the year ended March 31, 2004 against a loss of Rs 12.73 crore in the previous fiscal. Consolidated net sales during the reporting fiscal grew to Rs 817.49 crore compared with Rs 730.83 crore in 2002-03, a company release said here.																								Net profit for the quarter ended March 31, 2004 was up at Rs 13.30 crore against Rs 7.45 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. Net sales were up at Rs 295.26 crore (Rs 219.81 crore). 																								The turnaround has been possible due to a multi-pronged strategy of exploring new markets, increasing margins and reducing costs, KEC managing director Ramesh Chandak said. 																								The companys current order-book position stands at over Rs 2,000 crore with export orders to the tune of around Rs 1,300 crore.																								KEC said it expected the domestic order flow to be maintained in the coming years and it would continue its efforts on obtaining restoration business orders. 
